[Without isolation of virus or detection of viral nucleic acid, it is difficult to say what strain of Ebola is infecting the bats and when they became infected. - Mod.LK

The Ebolavirus Reston strain does occur in monkeys and pigs in the Philippines, but although it kills monkeys it is harmless for humans -- see ProMED archives, e.g. Ebola-Reston, porcine - Philippines (09): (BU) culling 20090305.0910. - Mod.JW]

